## 7. CODE REVIEW & CRITIQUE SYSTEMS

Perform self-reviews on all changes before marking tasks as completed.

### 7.1: Visual Integrity Review
* Evaluate layout adjustments against the **Composition Engine** (asymmetry, offsets, negative space) in `.antigravityrules`.
* Ensure that no bento box grids, saturated gradients, or centered layouts are introduced (Absolute Blacklist violations).

### 7.2: Performance Audit
* Verify that animations do not trigger layout thrashing. Avoid updating DOM properties like `offsetWidth` or `offsetTop` inside animation requestAnimationFrame loops.
* Check that GSAP animations use hardware-accelerated transforms (`x`, `y`, `rotation`, `scale`) instead of standard layout variables (`left`, `top`, `width`, `height`).
* Verify that ScrollTrigger elements are properly killed and cleaned up when components unmount to prevent memory leaks.

### 7.3: HSL Color Verification
* Ensure all styling references use HSL coordinates defined in the design tokens: e.g. `color: hsl(var(--color-ink-hue), var(--color-ink-sat), var(--color-ink-light))`.
* Do not write hardcoded hex values (`#ff0000`) or standard CSS color names (`red`).

