## 15. LESSONS FROM THE BEST FRENCH DEVELOPERS (Full Reference)

### Bruno Simon Portfolio Breakdown
* World Architecture: Built entirely inside a WebGL viewport container. Static content is layered programmatically inside canvas bounding coordinates.
* Rapier Integration: Objects fall, bounce, slide, and react to cursor collisions. Restitution parameters are set at 0.45.
* Resource Loader: Preloads all GLTF meshes dynamically, displaying percentage text updates.

### Sébastien Lempens Immersive Architecture
* sound sprites: Coordinates clicks, sweeps, and background loops inside a central sound configuration object.
* Entry Timeline: Plays ambient tracks only when the user clicks the mute toggle to dismiss the loader screen.
* Typography constraints: Suisse Intl is locked to uppercase headings with tight tracking values (`letter-spacing: -0.04em`).

### RXK Studio Repeatable Techniques
* Echo Text: Custom hover effect that duplicates display headlines and animates offsets.
* Zero-padding lists: Numbers list entries with double digits (e.g. `01`, `02`, `03`) in monospace fonts.
* Border styling: Flat grids featuring subtle 1px border lines and absolute zero spacing padding coordinates.

### Thomas Aufresne Restraint Standards
* Typography layout: Layout hierarchy is set using font size variations instead of color or decorative images.
* Background styling: Restricted to solid obsidian `#0a0a0a` or beige surfaces with thin layouts.
* Navigation: Small utility tags arranged in asymmetrical columns.

### Aristide Benoist Interaction Standards
* Lerp Loops: Cursor coordinates update inside a requestAnimationFrame tick with a 0.08 damping coefficient.
* Frame Rate Constraints: Animations check for frame drops and adjust render scales if frames drop below 50fps.
* Vanilla JS Setup: Rejects heavy framework loaders in favor of lightweight vanilla elements to maintain 100ms response latencies.

