## 17. STEP-BY-STEP REFACTORING EXAMPLES FOR POPULAR LIBRARIES

### 17.1: GSAP & ScrollTrigger Refactoring Setup
When refactoring components that leverage GSAP and ScrollTrigger:
* Step 1: Initialize the timeline and register the plugins.
* Step 2: Set up the scroll trigger coordinates (trigger, start, end, scrub).
* Step 3: Check that coordinates use relative clamp variables rather than hardcoded sizes.
* Step 4: Write clean cleanup loops inside components unmount lifecycle functions:
```javascript
export function registerScrollAnimation(triggerElement, targetElement) {
  gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);
  
  const ctx = gsap.context(() => {
    gsap.to(targetElement, {
      x: 100,
      scrollTrigger: {
        trigger: triggerElement,
        start: "top bottom",
        end: "bottom top",
        scrub: true
      }
    });
  });
  
  return () => ctx.revert(); // cleanly kills all triggers
}
```

### 17.2: Matter.js Physics Engine Rebuild Workflow
When refactoringMatter.js loops for sticker walls:
* Step 1: Create engine and world modules.
* Step 2: Declare grounds and boundaries matching container dimensions.
* Step 3: Add objects with slight randomized rotation constants.
* Step 4: Hook animation tickers, syncing positions back to absolute HTML elements:
```javascript
export function rebuildPhysicsEngine(containerElement, items) {
  const engine = Matter.Engine.create();
  const world = engine.world;
  
  // Set boundaries...
  const ground = Matter.Bodies.rectangle(
    containerElement.clientWidth / 2,
    containerElement.clientHeight + 10,
    containerElement.clientWidth,
    20,
    { isStatic: true }
  );
  Matter.World.add(world, ground);
  
  // Update loop...
  (function update() {
    Matter.Engine.update(engine);
    requestAnimationFrame(update);
  })();
}
```

### 17.3: Howler.js Sprite Configuration Setup
When setting up audio managers inside interactive elements:
* Step 1: Declare paths and format lists.
* Step 2: Define exact offset markers in milliseconds inside the sprite property:
```javascript
const sound = new Howl({
  src: ['sounds.mp3'],
  sprite: {
    laser: [0, 1000],
    winner: [2000, 3500]
  }
});
```

